value.0: This statue depicts Kelemvor, Lord of the Dead. He seeks to impart justices among the dead in an even-handed and fair manner. Reflecting upon Kelemvor's finely carved depiction reminds his followers that death is but a part of life, and it could be accepted instead of feared.
The vestments of the Doomguide of Kelemvor.
A hand and a half sword consecrated in the rituals of Kelemvor, Lord of the Dead.
This holy symbol of Kelemvor was of very fine craftsmanship.

This bed has a beaten straw mattress, lined with well worn cotton sheets and covered with a worn woolen blanket.  Tended quite well, washed and scented, you will not find any bedbugs living here.  Soft enough to allow even the most hard adventurer a decent nights rest.

These iron gauntlets appear to have seen some use, particularly in settling conflicts without resorting to the sword.
Wearing gloves is usually just a matter of fashion, since they do not afford any protection unless infused with magic.
This is a hammered iron helmet. It should provide a suitable amount of protection.
This is a hammered iron large shield. It should provide a suitable amount of protection.
This well made mace was crafted during the Interregnum and still functions exceptionally, even though the civil war ended a few years ago.
The mace is a derivative of the basic club, consisting of a stone or metal head mounted on the end of a wooden shaft.  The weight of the head greatly increases the force of the impact.
This well made warhammer was crafted during the Interregnum and still functions exceptionally, even though the civil war ended a few years ago.
Originally adapted from the tools of laborers and craftsmen, the warhammer is a far-heavier variant of the sledge and is no longer suitable for anything but combat.
This is a dagger with silver inlaid in the iron blade.
This is a sword that has been forged with silver in the iron blade.
This holy symbol of Kelemvor was of very fine craftsmanship.
This is a fine incense, made with quality perfumes.

As a follower of a specific deity there will be rites and practices associated with that deity. One thing that is common to all is the requirement to use the appropriate holy symbol when calling upon the deity's power. 

The Holy Symbol for each deity may be different and should be obtained from the appropriate temple. The holy symbol for a ranger or druid may be somthing sacred to the caster rather than a church sanctioned object.

This book contains a list of spells for which a practitioner must have a Holy Symbol equipped. 

In addition there are some spell which require other components. These are usually found in the same places arcane magic users obtain components.

This book is useful for Clerics, Druids, Rangers and Paladins.

Garlic is well known as a herb for flavoring foods and treating heat stroke among the preasantry. It is also used to repulse vampires.
This tent is of low quality make. It seems as though it will help when the temperature drops, but the materials won't hold up in rain or wind.

This is a blessed reliquary, prepared for use by paladins to imbue their Holy Avengers.

A Blessed Reliquary takes up 1/10 available modification slots for a Holy Avenger.

This is a Crystal Skull, intended for use by paladins to make their Holy Avengers more effective against undead.

A Crystal Skull uses 1/10 available modification slots.

This is a soft ingot of silver alloy meant for paladins to apply to their Holy Avenger.

Gilding Silver takes up 1/10 of the available modification slots for a Holy Avenger.

These holy scriptures are filled with fables from the recent Time of Troubles.

If used by a cleric to bless armor or a shield, Holy Scriptures take up 1/2 available modification slots.

This is Martyr's blood, which is reserved for use by paladins to grant their Holy Swords defending properties.

Martyr's Blood uses 1/10 available item slot modifications.

This is a Netherworld Stone, prepared for use by Paladins to affect ghosts with their Holy Avengers.

A Netherworld Stone takes up 1/10 available modification slots for a Holy Avenger.

This is a sacred pattern which may be incorporated in a cloak by a tailor.

A Sacred Pattern takes up 1/1 available modification slots.

This vial of Holy Water will cause damage to undead creatures if thrown.

If imbibed, it is believed to protect against certain evil spells or effects.
